WEBVTT

00:00:28.134 --> 00:00:30.615
Welcome to the Yahowah blog and back here

00:00:30.635 --> 00:00:31.736
in the library studio.

00:00:31.797 --> 00:00:33.137
I'm your host, Craig Winn.

00:00:33.798 --> 00:00:37.200
We have been continuing a series called

00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:38.240
Return to the Garden.

00:00:38.301 --> 00:00:40.883
It is among the most important stories

00:00:40.902 --> 00:00:42.844
that I could possibly share with you.

00:00:43.524 --> 00:00:47.366
It goes back to a realization that the

00:00:47.527 --> 00:00:51.350
garden experience was almost a hundred and

00:00:51.409 --> 00:00:52.631
eighty degrees different.

00:00:53.307 --> 00:00:55.247
than it has been perceived all of these

00:00:55.287 --> 00:00:55.688
years.

00:00:56.529 --> 00:01:00.969
And that our path towards God and his

00:01:01.009 --> 00:01:04.989
interactions with us are also a hundred

00:01:05.030 --> 00:01:07.850
and eighty degrees different than what the

00:01:07.911 --> 00:01:09.290
religious have proposed.

00:01:10.290 --> 00:01:12.391
The story before I continue,

00:01:12.471 --> 00:01:14.671
and we're now in Yasha'yah Isaiah,

00:01:15.292 --> 00:01:18.393
as he is describing the process of us

00:01:18.492 --> 00:01:19.772
returning to the garden,

00:01:20.552 --> 00:01:22.174
is that when you look at the garden

00:01:22.233 --> 00:01:22.853
experience,

00:01:24.161 --> 00:01:27.382
There was no Eve.

00:01:27.402 --> 00:01:29.542
There was no discernible fruit.

00:01:31.102 --> 00:01:34.882
There were two trees that heretofore no

00:01:34.942 --> 00:01:37.403
one had properly identified, but we have.

00:01:39.364 --> 00:01:44.084
We have man being taken from all of

00:01:44.125 --> 00:01:46.986
the other animals that existed on earth

00:01:47.525 --> 00:01:51.486
and being given one unique difference.

00:01:52.531 --> 00:01:56.453
one added attribute that made this man

00:01:56.914 --> 00:01:59.876
potentially better than any other animal

00:01:59.975 --> 00:02:02.037
in terms of being a potential for a

00:02:02.076 --> 00:02:02.996
companion with God.

00:02:03.757 --> 00:02:06.778
And that is that Adam was given a

00:02:06.838 --> 00:02:09.100
nesama, a conscience,

00:02:09.461 --> 00:02:11.981
in addition to what all other animals have

00:02:12.222 --> 00:02:13.883
as a consciousness,

00:02:13.962 --> 00:02:15.364
which is our nephesh soul.

00:02:15.783 --> 00:02:18.425
So a nesama in a difference to a

00:02:18.485 --> 00:02:20.567
nephesh soul.

00:02:21.067 --> 00:02:21.326
And then

00:02:23.159 --> 00:02:24.599
With that addition,

00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:29.361
then we were a less robust,

00:02:30.562 --> 00:02:33.703
smaller dimensionally version of God,

00:02:33.782 --> 00:02:34.424
man was.

00:02:34.764 --> 00:02:39.044
That's the image there that with a nesama,

00:02:39.064 --> 00:02:40.145
with a conscience,

00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:43.346
then we were in the image of God.

00:02:44.447 --> 00:02:48.288
It's very much like a blueprint is to

00:02:48.367 --> 00:02:48.807
a building.

00:02:50.236 --> 00:02:51.877
The blueprint is in two dimensions.

00:02:51.978 --> 00:02:54.638
The building is actually infinitely larger

00:02:54.677 --> 00:02:56.739
than the blueprint because it's in three

00:02:56.778 --> 00:02:57.359
dimensions.

00:02:58.639 --> 00:03:00.939
But in God's case,

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:03.260
we're three-dimensional and he's

00:03:03.300 --> 00:03:04.181
seven-dimensional.

00:03:04.221 --> 00:03:08.442
So it's that infinite increase times an

00:03:08.502 --> 00:03:10.103
infinite increase times an infinite

00:03:10.143 --> 00:03:12.782
increase times an infinite increase or an

00:03:12.883 --> 00:03:17.525
infinity to the fourth power to go from

00:03:17.544 --> 00:03:18.824
the third to the seventh dimension.

00:03:19.875 --> 00:03:22.576
So this is already a different rendering

00:03:22.638 --> 00:03:25.680
of what you've heard than what has been

00:03:25.860 --> 00:03:27.262
presented previously.

00:03:30.024 --> 00:03:32.667
The single most important aspect of all of

00:03:32.706 --> 00:03:35.549
this is the proper understanding of what

00:03:35.729 --> 00:03:37.730
Gan represents.

00:03:37.790 --> 00:03:38.651
It's Gan Eden.

00:03:40.173 --> 00:03:44.037
Gan is a sheltered, covered, protected,

00:03:44.576 --> 00:03:45.258
concealed,

00:03:46.764 --> 00:03:49.944
Environment that is conducive to life,

00:03:50.324 --> 00:03:53.504
sheltered, protected.

00:03:53.525 --> 00:03:55.265
Environment that is conducive to life.

00:03:56.485 --> 00:03:58.725
This makes Gan Eden,

00:03:59.826 --> 00:04:03.146
the Garden of Great Joy,

00:04:03.287 --> 00:04:06.228
a microcosm of our planet, of Earth.

00:04:07.487 --> 00:04:07.828
You see,

00:04:07.967 --> 00:04:11.449
Earth is unique in all of the known

00:04:11.528 --> 00:04:11.989
universe.

00:04:13.263 --> 00:04:14.883
Our galaxy is unique.

00:04:14.924 --> 00:04:17.225
It's in the center of a huge bubble,

00:04:17.625 --> 00:04:20.987
unaffected by all of the chaos that is

00:04:21.028 --> 00:04:22.788
happening in other galaxies,

00:04:22.869 --> 00:04:24.750
the two trillion of them all around us.

00:04:25.531 --> 00:04:27.192
And we're in the perfect place in our

00:04:27.252 --> 00:04:31.434
galaxy to have access to the heavy

00:04:31.494 --> 00:04:36.336
elements so that mankind can be created

00:04:36.377 --> 00:04:37.718
from the dust of the earth,

00:04:37.757 --> 00:04:38.658
at least our bodies.

00:04:40.663 --> 00:04:42.985
perfect environment to minimize constant

00:04:43.024 --> 00:04:48.387
bombardment of cosmic rays and of neutron

00:04:48.447 --> 00:04:51.230
stars and supernova and all of that and

00:04:51.250 --> 00:04:52.750
yet not so far enough,

00:04:53.651 --> 00:04:57.533
so far out that there isn't hasn't been

00:04:57.553 --> 00:04:59.795
the explosion of first generation stars,

00:05:00.136 --> 00:05:01.997
providing the hella heavy elements that

00:05:02.036 --> 00:05:04.197
are necessary, not only for our planet,

00:05:04.218 --> 00:05:05.119
but for life itself.

00:05:06.663 --> 00:05:10.848
And protected from all of the bombardment

00:05:10.887 --> 00:05:13.891
of other galaxies because of this bubble

00:05:13.930 --> 00:05:14.951
that we happen to be in.

00:05:15.052 --> 00:05:17.454
And then you look at the Earth itself

00:05:17.495 --> 00:05:20.218
with its moon and its star and its

00:05:20.577 --> 00:05:24.541
orbit, and it's the perfect star for life.

00:05:26.137 --> 00:05:27.017
A red dwarf,

00:05:27.098 --> 00:05:29.660
as are so many stars as you move

00:05:29.699 --> 00:05:31.259
further out in galaxies that are too

00:05:31.319 --> 00:05:32.641
unpredictable, too unreliable.

00:05:33.440 --> 00:05:37.803
It is not such a massive star that

00:05:37.923 --> 00:05:42.146
it would be way too short-lived for life

00:05:42.165 --> 00:05:43.266
to develop on our planet.

00:05:43.745 --> 00:05:44.966
It's the perfect size star.

00:05:46.038 --> 00:05:47.379
Perfect demeanor of a star.

00:05:48.038 --> 00:05:49.478
And the Earth happens to be the perfect

00:05:49.619 --> 00:05:50.819
distance from that star.

00:05:50.860 --> 00:05:55.081
You see what happens with Venus just a

00:05:55.141 --> 00:05:57.161
wee bit closer and Mars just a wee

00:05:57.201 --> 00:05:57.923
bit further out.

00:05:59.242 --> 00:06:02.283
But it is also our molten core that

00:06:02.803 --> 00:06:03.324
spins,

00:06:03.365 --> 00:06:05.105
creating a magnetic field that is so

00:06:05.165 --> 00:06:06.966
essential to life on this planet.

00:06:07.786 --> 00:06:09.427
And, you know, Mars doesn't have one.

00:06:09.466 --> 00:06:10.807
Maybe it had one long ago,

00:06:10.827 --> 00:06:11.947
but it doesn't have one anymore.

00:06:12.733 --> 00:06:14.016
And without it,

00:06:14.136 --> 00:06:16.658
there is no protection for cosmic rays and

00:06:16.718 --> 00:06:19.463
life cannot develop.

00:06:19.483 --> 00:06:22.666
You have to have enormous amounts of

00:06:22.726 --> 00:06:23.067
water.

00:06:23.266 --> 00:06:24.869
And again,

00:06:24.908 --> 00:06:27.012
in this Goldilocks zone where water can be

00:06:27.211 --> 00:06:28.314
liquid on the surface,

00:06:28.954 --> 00:06:31.398
that is very precisely tuned.

00:06:32.423 --> 00:06:35.286
And you have to have a moon abnormally

00:06:35.365 --> 00:06:38.370
large that creates tides.

00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:40.531
Otherwise, life is impossible.

00:06:40.572 --> 00:06:43.375
You have to have Teutonic plates that move

00:06:43.415 --> 00:06:47.199
the crust for life to be possible.

00:06:47.439 --> 00:06:50.242
You have to have a giant planet that's

00:06:50.262 --> 00:06:51.463
a gaseous giant.

00:06:52.314 --> 00:06:53.975
that is the perfect distance actually

00:06:54.076 --> 00:06:56.156
outside of the orbit of the planet for

00:06:56.197 --> 00:06:57.899
it to absorb the shock of all of

00:06:57.918 --> 00:07:02.040
the crashing meteors and comets that would

00:07:02.081 --> 00:07:04.843
otherwise destroy life on the planet like

00:07:04.882 --> 00:07:07.685
when this planet was hit sixty million

00:07:07.725 --> 00:07:09.685
years ago to end the reign of the

00:07:09.706 --> 00:07:10.286
dinosaurs.

00:07:12.267 --> 00:07:16.831
It's just one checklist after another that

00:07:16.870 --> 00:07:19.091
makes the planet just so extraordinarily

00:07:19.172 --> 00:07:21.593
rare that it is

00:07:23.168 --> 00:07:25.910
a sheltered and protective garden that is

00:07:25.970 --> 00:07:28.430
conducive to life.

00:07:28.451 --> 00:07:29.951
Eden is the microcosm of it.

00:07:31.413 --> 00:07:32.733
The other thing that's interesting in this

00:07:32.812 --> 00:07:39.036
regard is the correlation between Eden and

00:07:39.096 --> 00:07:41.978
Gan Eden, Gan from Ghana,

00:07:42.057 --> 00:07:43.598
meaning sheltered and enclosed,

00:07:43.637 --> 00:07:46.920
protective place for a garden, and Sukkah.

00:07:47.644 --> 00:07:48.644
which is from Sakak,

00:07:48.685 --> 00:07:50.865
which has the exact same definition,

00:07:51.365 --> 00:07:56.487
to be sheltered, protected, covered.

00:07:56.528 --> 00:08:00.189
So what we're actually doing with God's

00:08:00.230 --> 00:08:02.069
plan as it's laid out in the Towrah

00:08:02.550 --> 00:08:05.271
is we're going from the garden back to

00:08:05.312 --> 00:08:07.632
the garden over six thousand years.

00:08:07.672 --> 00:08:10.153
So we end up in the garden over

00:08:10.653 --> 00:08:12.413
the seventh thousandth year.

00:08:13.093 --> 00:08:14.274
And that's exactly where we are.

00:08:14.966 --> 00:08:17.047
We are just seven and a half years

00:08:17.107 --> 00:08:21.708
now away from our beginning of the seventh

00:08:21.747 --> 00:08:23.269
millennium man.

00:08:24.408 --> 00:08:26.389
And it is on Sukkah that we will

00:08:26.430 --> 00:08:27.410
return to the garden.

00:08:29.471 --> 00:08:31.031
So why were we kicked out of the

00:08:31.050 --> 00:08:31.432
garden?

00:08:32.611 --> 00:08:33.511
Why six steps?

00:08:33.652 --> 00:08:35.633
Why six thousand years in between?

00:08:36.852 --> 00:08:39.254
And why are we being invited back to

00:08:39.293 --> 00:08:39.714
the garden?

00:08:39.734 --> 00:08:42.514
That is something that I'm positive that

00:08:42.554 --> 00:08:44.056
no one else has ever shared with you

00:08:44.096 --> 00:08:44.416
before.

00:08:46.846 --> 00:08:48.948
And the reason is that in the garden,

00:08:50.650 --> 00:08:53.955
man was a flop.

00:08:53.975 --> 00:08:55.836
We failed not because of sin.

00:08:55.856 --> 00:08:57.298
There was no original sin.

00:08:57.318 --> 00:09:01.683
That's Roman Catholic malarkey.

00:09:01.764 --> 00:09:01.985
We've,

00:09:03.749 --> 00:09:06.311
failed in the garden because we didn't do

00:09:06.530 --> 00:09:08.633
any of the things that Yahowah needed us

00:09:08.692 --> 00:09:12.056
to do for us to be able to

00:09:12.096 --> 00:09:14.217
be allowed out of the garden in a

00:09:14.278 --> 00:09:17.419
manner that God could actually take us off

00:09:17.480 --> 00:09:19.142
of this planet and go explore the

00:09:19.201 --> 00:09:21.144
universe, which was his intent.

00:09:21.163 --> 00:09:23.184
You see,

00:09:24.546 --> 00:09:27.749
this universe that we're in is so enormous

00:09:28.669 --> 00:09:29.650
that mankind,

00:09:30.902 --> 00:09:32.943
after all of this time has only managed

00:09:32.964 --> 00:09:33.964
to go to our moon.

00:09:34.104 --> 00:09:37.767
And only that what's six or seven times

00:09:37.886 --> 00:09:40.229
and the longest being less than a week.

00:09:41.509 --> 00:09:44.552
And the fact that we're pretending to go

00:09:44.572 --> 00:09:47.173
back is only because just like the last

00:09:47.214 --> 00:09:48.375
time we had a reason we wanted to

00:09:48.394 --> 00:09:49.335
beat the Soviets.

00:09:49.375 --> 00:09:51.197
This time we want to beat the Chinese,

00:09:51.657 --> 00:09:52.658
but no one's going to live on the

00:09:52.677 --> 00:09:54.099
moon.

00:09:54.178 --> 00:09:55.399
It's way too toxic.

00:09:56.620 --> 00:09:59.844
And the moon is three days distant at

00:09:59.943 --> 00:10:02.125
our present traveling speeds.

00:10:02.225 --> 00:10:04.408
And Mars,

00:10:04.488 --> 00:10:07.410
even at the best point where our orbits

00:10:08.010 --> 00:10:10.533
get sort of a line, which happens every,

00:10:10.552 --> 00:10:10.712
what,

00:10:10.753 --> 00:10:14.255
twenty four months or twenty two months,

00:10:14.317 --> 00:10:16.899
I think is is the period almost two

00:10:16.938 --> 00:10:20.922
years, is that it at that point,

00:10:22.222 --> 00:10:22.443
it's

00:10:23.894 --> 00:10:26.575
six to nine months en route.

00:10:29.076 --> 00:10:32.118
But the travel time, the distance as well,

00:10:32.258 --> 00:10:34.158
hugely disparate.

00:10:35.460 --> 00:10:37.561
The fact is no one is ever going

00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:38.902
to go to Mars to live.

00:10:39.182 --> 00:10:40.741
Elon Musk is just flat out wrong.

00:10:40.942 --> 00:10:42.462
And I'm sure he knows it,

00:10:42.503 --> 00:10:44.303
but he doesn't want to admit it because

00:10:44.323 --> 00:10:46.004
then what else does he do with SpaceX?

00:10:46.245 --> 00:10:47.725
What does he do with his money?

00:10:47.745 --> 00:10:48.767
What does he do with his life?

00:10:49.846 --> 00:10:51.288
But no one's going to Mars to live.

00:10:51.947 --> 00:10:53.308
We may one time,

00:10:54.201 --> 00:10:55.783
send people to Mars to die,

00:10:56.243 --> 00:10:58.485
but they're not going to live there.

00:10:59.326 --> 00:10:59.946
And beyond that,

00:11:00.246 --> 00:11:02.849
there is a zero percent chance that human

00:11:02.889 --> 00:11:04.350
beings will ever even travel there.

00:11:04.389 --> 00:11:05.951
That's how great the distances are.

00:11:06.451 --> 00:11:06.611
Now,

00:11:06.692 --> 00:11:08.594
if we were to try to travel to

00:11:08.634 --> 00:11:10.275
the nearest star,

00:11:10.895 --> 00:11:16.741
which is a lousy triplet of red dwarfs,

00:11:18.004 --> 00:11:20.405
It would take seventy thousand years to

00:11:20.426 --> 00:11:21.386
get there.

00:11:21.447 --> 00:11:24.089
Seventy thousand years.

00:11:25.529 --> 00:11:29.734
And after a matter of one year,

00:11:31.274 --> 00:11:33.777
the human being wouldn't survive.

00:11:33.996 --> 00:11:35.958
Our bodies would deteriorate to the point

00:11:36.599 --> 00:11:38.201
that it wouldn't be possible.

00:11:38.221 --> 00:11:39.621
We can't survive one year,

00:11:39.662 --> 00:11:40.942
my seventy thousand years.

00:11:40.962 --> 00:11:43.164
One of the reasons why Mars isn't doable.

00:11:43.804 --> 00:11:45.427
It can't get away from Earth's gravity.

00:11:47.207 --> 00:11:49.649
for more than a year and expect to

00:11:49.668 --> 00:11:50.149
survive it.

00:11:51.129 --> 00:11:54.131
So this planet is unique.

00:11:54.172 --> 00:11:55.493
Now we know we have a universe of

00:11:55.552 --> 00:11:56.533
two trillion stars,

00:11:57.114 --> 00:11:59.576
none of which we can reach.

00:12:00.355 --> 00:12:01.756
Not two trillion stars,

00:12:01.777 --> 00:12:02.957
two trillion galaxies,

00:12:03.018 --> 00:12:05.600
each with a few hundred billion stars,

00:12:05.659 --> 00:12:10.523
each with hundreds of planets and moons.

00:12:11.563 --> 00:12:13.924
We can't get there to any of them.

00:12:13.945 --> 00:12:14.765
But God created it.

00:12:16.211 --> 00:12:17.152
And he wants us to see it.

00:12:17.172 --> 00:12:17.972
He wants to share it.

00:12:18.332 --> 00:12:21.033
What good is something that magnificent if

00:12:21.073 --> 00:12:22.693
you don't have someone to share it with?

00:12:23.333 --> 00:12:24.575
So now back to the garden.

00:12:25.274 --> 00:12:28.336
What did Yahowah want from Adam,

00:12:28.355 --> 00:12:30.836
from this man that he gave a conscience

00:12:30.856 --> 00:12:35.739
so he could be smarter than any of

00:12:35.759 --> 00:12:37.538
the animals that can actually think.

00:12:37.558 --> 00:12:37.639
And

00:12:40.984 --> 00:12:43.184
The first thing he said of man,

00:12:43.245 --> 00:12:45.865
he wanted man to work, to engage,

00:12:45.885 --> 00:12:47.547
to do something, to make a contribution.

00:12:47.586 --> 00:12:49.206
He's not looking for a dependent.

00:12:49.827 --> 00:12:50.607
Adam was a dependent.

00:12:50.628 --> 00:12:51.847
He didn't contribute anything.

00:12:52.788 --> 00:12:54.769
Men have heretofore,

00:12:55.269 --> 00:12:57.931
you could count on two hands,

00:12:58.051 --> 00:13:02.552
maybe two feet and two hands if you

00:13:02.613 --> 00:13:04.594
count fingers and toes of the people who

00:13:04.614 --> 00:13:06.354
have actually productively engaged with

00:13:06.394 --> 00:13:09.294
Yahowah over these past six thousand years

00:13:10.096 --> 00:13:10.556
and only

00:13:12.437 --> 00:13:15.980
Two or three of them are really notable.

00:13:16.301 --> 00:13:18.461
Maybe a handful that are really notable

00:13:18.782 --> 00:13:20.363
that have made a tremendous contribution.

00:13:22.504 --> 00:13:24.586
The first who listened and did what God

00:13:24.625 --> 00:13:27.847
said is Noah.

00:13:28.187 --> 00:13:30.789
The next is Moshe.

00:13:33.371 --> 00:13:38.855
After that, you get to Dowd, David.

00:13:38.916 --> 00:13:39.556
Not a lot of people.

00:13:40.491 --> 00:13:41.873
you know, brief periods here and there,

00:13:41.893 --> 00:13:43.253
but to see it all the way through

00:13:43.312 --> 00:13:45.114
and make a major contribution is very few

00:13:45.153 --> 00:13:45.653
examples.

00:13:47.154 --> 00:13:48.956
So the first thing God wanted is somebody

00:13:49.456 --> 00:13:51.057
to work with him, to engage with him.

00:13:51.076 --> 00:13:52.336
God values work.

00:13:52.397 --> 00:13:55.979
He is always wanting to engage and to

00:13:56.038 --> 00:13:58.059
make a contribution to make things better.

00:13:58.679 --> 00:14:02.581
And mankind has not been good in that

